# Fixing Pop Sound

Change its value from 1 to 0
'''
sudo nano /sys/module/snd_hda_intel/parameters/power_save
'''

and Y to N to the this one
'''
sudo nano /sys/module/snd_hda_intel/parameters/power_save_controller
'''

If distortions(noise, buzzing, crackling ...) are gone, make it permanent, Then :

cd /etc/modprobe.d


Â and make a new file named: audio_disable_powersave.conf 

sudo nano audio_disable_powersave.conf
Then :

insert following in the conf file: 
options snd_hda_intel power_save=0



After then save it and reboot.


